&lt;p&gt;And then import that back into the styles.scss file.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;src/styles.scss&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&quot;0&quot; data-language=&quot;scss&quot; data-theme=&quot;github-light github-dark&quot;&gt;&lt;code data-language=&quot;scss&quot; data-theme=&quot;github-light github-dark&quot; style=&quot;display: grid;&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-line=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F97583&quot;&gt;@import&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;--shiki-light:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#9ECBFF&quot;&gt; &quot;src/styles/_dom.scss&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E4E8&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And in the material-overrides folder I will create a file for each Angular Material Component and override its default styles in there so they apply globally to my app.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;src/styles/material-overrides/_mat-icon.scss&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
